-- HSBC Interested in UniCredit Eastern European Businesses, Repubblica Says
-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2010-11-15T06:55:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-15/hsbc-may-be-interested-in-unicredit-businesses-repubblica-says.html
HSBC Group may be interested in
buying some of  UniCredit SpA’s  businesses in eastern Europe, la
Repubblica reported, without saying where it got the
information.  HSBC may also have hired lawyers in Italy to examine legal
issues of owning more than a 5 percent stake in the Italian
bank, according to Repubblica’s weekly business section.  Banco Santander SA and Societe Generale may have also
looked at buying some of the Italian bank’s activities,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Armorel Kenna in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net  